fromString:
All our tools use application logic classes ({{Context}}, {{Activity}}, etc.) by using the {{BaseTool}} class.

We need to make the tools observable, ui classes should then observe and change properties of the corresponding tool classes.

Offending occurences include but are not limited to:
h3. BaseTool
{code:java}
public BaseTool(Context context, ToolType toolType) { .. }
private void resetAndInitializeToolOptions() { ... }
public void hide() { ... }
public void toggleShowToolOptions() { ... }
private void dimBackground(boolean darken) { ... }
public boolean getToolOptionsAreShown() { ... }
{code}

h3. Why is this bad
* Most of our tool "unit" tests need an Activity or Context to work, therefor making them really slow
* It violates the SOLID principles
* Tools know about their observing views and even modify and setup them, therefore making it impossible to have more than one observing view at a time

h6. References
http://misko.hevery.com/attachments/Guide-Writing%20Testable%20Code.pdf

